The paper deals with the problem of finding sparsest k-TC-spanners, which involves graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the use of 2-TC-spanners for designing property testers, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
